article.description: Devonte Patterson had 21 points as Prairie View won its seventh consecutive game, beating Alabama State 65-58 on Saturday.
article.headline: Patterson lifts Prairie View past Alabama St. 65-58
article.linkText: Patterson lifts Prairie View past Alabama St. 65-58
article.story: PRAIRIE VIEW, Texas -- Devonte Patterson had 21 points as Prairie View won its seventh consecutive game, beating Alabama State 65-58 on Saturday. Antione Lister had 15 points for Prairie View (17-11, 13-2 Southwestern Athletic Conference). Gerard Andrus added 10 points and seven rebounds. Faite Williams had 9 points, 11 rebounds and eight assists. Austin Rogers had 12 points for the Hornets (8-20, 7-8). DJ Heath added 10 points. Jacoby Ross had seven assists. Tyrese Robinson had 3 points and 15 rebounds. The Panthers evened the season series against the Hornets with the win. Alabama State defeated Prairie View 52-49 on Feb. 1. Prairie View faces Alabama A&M at home on Monday. Alabama State takes on Texas Southern on the road on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
